# Test Results & Analysis

## 1. Speed Calculation Accuracy

The IR sensor-based speed measurement was validated against a manually timed stopwatch baseline across 10 trials at varying motor PWM values.

| Trial | Motor PWM | Stopwatch Speed (km/h) | System Measured Speed (km/h) | Error (%) |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | 100 | 2.3 | 2.4 | 4.3% |
| 2 | 130 | 3.5 | 3.6 | 2.9% |
| 3 | 160 | 4.7 | 4.8 | 2.1% |
| 4 | 190 | 6.0 | 6.1 | 1.7% |
| 5 | 220 | 7.4 | 7.2 | 2.7% |
| 6 | 255 | 8.6 | 8.5 | 1.2% |
| 7 | 100 | 2.4 | 2.3 | 4.2% |
| 8 | 160 | 4.6 | 4.7 | 2.2% |
| 9 | 220 | 7.3 | 7.4 | 1.4% |
| 10 | 255 | 8.5 | 8.6 | 1.2% |

**Average measurement error: ~2.4%** — within acceptable tolerance for a low-cost IR sensor prototype.

*(Replace these numbers with your own measured values — use a stopwatch + the Serial Monitor side by side and log at least 8-10 trials.)*

